    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Melee Tactics Toolbox pg. 19</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 10 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 4 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> grapple</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Simple</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Axes</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>This weapon acts as a kumade, but the handle consists of bamboo sections held together by a taut rope running through the center. Releasing the rope is a standard action that provokes attacks of opportunity and causes the weapon to collapse into a bundle that fits into a backpack. Reassembling the collapsible kumade requires a full-round action that provokes attacks of opportunity.</p>"
